SIMPLE: ance
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: -ance
<hw>-ance</hw>. <ety>[F. <ets>-ance</ets>, fr. L. <ets>-antia</ets> and
also fr. <ets>-entia</ets>.]</ety> <def>A suffix signifying action;
also, quality or state; <as>as, assist<ex>ance</ex>,
resist<ex>ance</ex>, appear<ex>ance</ex>, eleg<ex>ance</ex></as>. See
<er>-ancy</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ All recently adopted words of this class take either
-<xex>ance</xex> or -<xex>ence</xex>, according to the Latin
spelling.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

